                            <comment id="14510756" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Fri, 24 Apr 2015 10:07:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the analysis, JAXRSDefaultFaultOutInterceptor is meant to support non-JAXRS (CXF-specific) interceptors that may throw the exceptions but users have registered JAX-RS Exception mappers.&lt;br/&gt;
In this case it is interfering with the JAX-RS flow - so I&apos;ve updated the code for this interceptor skip its processing in case of the unmapped second-time exceptions thrown from JAX-RS filters/interceptors&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
